decision_conditions:
No part of the superstructures shall be constructed until details of a scheme of renewable energy technology measures has been submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority. The details shall include:
a) the nature, location, specification and operational details of each element of the scheme, including any machinery/apparatus;
b) an energy assessment confirming that the scheme will provide for no less than 8% on-site COH reduction, as detailed in the ‘Energy Strategy Report’ (Rev C, dated July 2010);
c) a management plan and maintenance strategy/schedule for the continuing operation of the renewable energy technology measures.
The renewable energy measures shall be implemented as approved, and a copy of each building’s Energy Performance Certificate shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority,
before the building is first occupied. The renewable energy measures shall be managed and operated thereafter in accordance with the approved details.
